\\subsection*\{Twitter\}\
Twitter is a microblogging online social network, were users post messages seen by other users. This message passing is referred to as \\textit\{tweeting\} where each message is referred to as a \\textit\{tweet\}. The length of each message is limited to 140 characters. By default messages are publicly available, although users have the right to close the access to their authorized followers.\
\
Each user is provided with a profile that including user specific information, such as name, user name, a short bio, location, URL and photo. The tweets are posted on their timeline, where other users can like or make comments.\
\
In order to analyze Twitter data we need to create a Twitter Application. When the application is created, we get access to Keys and Access Tokens for authentication. By authorizing the t-hoarder kit using the tokens, access to the Twitter API is obtained. \
